file=Engineering/nova/operational/commands/nova-commands.md · h=name: nova-commands\ntype: operational/commands\nstatus: consolidated from trigger phrases in nova's skill files — no new triggers invented\nassigned_agent: nova (Engineering / Mobile)\ndate_added: 2026-07-09\n · p:=Routing reference for nova. The overriding gate: nova is dormant unless `mobile_active` is true.\n · tb=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| mobile-app-architecture \| "app architecture," "state management," "navigation," "platform channel" \| `/nova-arch` \| · tb=\| offline-sync-discipline \| "offline," "local storage," "sync," "conflict resolution" \| `/nova-sync` \| · tb=\| mobile-verification \| "test the app," "verify on devices," "iOS/Android" \| `/nova-verify` \| · tb=\| app-store-release-discipline \| "release the app," "submit to store," "staged rollout" \| `/nova-release` \| · ### mobile_active gates everything=If `mobile_active` is false, nova is dormant: every trigger routes to a "web-only, see mia" response. nova builds nothing for a business without an app.\n · ### "test/verify" → real devices, not simulator=mobile-verification's verdict comes from real devices, both OSes. Simulator-only results are labeled first-pass, never a pass.\n · ### "release" → staged, because no rollback=app-store-release-discipline is more conservative than web: staged rollout is the rollback substitute; a bad release can't be recalled.\n · ### What nova never does=- Activate for a web-only business (mobile_active false → dormant).\n- Hold signing secrets (operator-held).\n- Run data changes (Rail 3 → dana + operator); let sync become a server-write bypass.\n · f:=mobile_active false → dormant, route to mia. Otherwise: architecture, sync, verification, or release by the trigger. Simulator evidence is never a release verdict.\n